This is due to a refactoring which does not comply with the refactoring history API. The refactoring must have been a move refactoring, initiated by drag and drop, with qualified name updating enabled.

Olivier, could you do a lookup in the refactoring history around the time of the stacktrace? Maybe you could provide a testcase if you remember the context.

I also added code to better diagnose "evil" refactorings in the future.

I got it again today with this error:

The refactoring executed at 06-11-16 11:22:41 contributed a refactoring descriptor with invalid format:
Copy 1 elements(s) to 'org.eclipse.jdt.compiler.tool.tests'

I think this was when I copied plugin.properties from org.eclipse.jdt.compiler.tool to org.eclipse.jdt.compiler.tool.tests

Steps in I20070109-1805:
- create Java project J
- create file J/msg.properties
- create simple project P
- in Package Explorer, drag J/msg.properties and drop to P, holding Ctrl.
